''CHIEF OF STAFF--STANLEY PEPPERS''
Perhaps more urgently: your Surgeon has gone missing. He's a bit of a strange character, haha! My understanding was that he was supposed to be here with me when you awoke to do a post-op inspection, but uh...haha! This is just the way things are!

[[Next | 1-2]]


:: \ 1-2 {"position":"1700,800","size":"100,100"}
''CHIEF OF STAFF--STANLEY PEPPERS''
Basically, we need to have your Surgeon take a look at you before you start leading our country to greatness! But it's up to you: I can walk you to Director Ume, or you can try to find your Surgeon yourself. What's your preference?

[[You can take me to Director Ume. Let's not waste time.]]
[[I'm going to be honest: I'm a little confused about what all is going on, and a stroll by myself doesn't sound so bad right now.]]


:: \ 1-3 {"position":"1600,1100","size":"100,100"}
''CHIEF OF STAFF--STANLEY PEPPERS''
Director Ume! So glad you're still here doing...this. Haha! Per your request, I have brought you the new President of the United States. Ask and you shall receive! 

Mr. President, this is Director of the Office of Management and Budget, Quentin Ume. I will leave you two to it while I try to address the mouse problem in my office. How did they even get here! Haha!

[[Chief Peppers leaves | 1-4]]


:: \ 1-4 {"position":"1600,1200","size":"100,100"}
''DIRECTOR, OFFICE OF MANAGEMENT & BUDGET--QUENTIN UME''
Pleasure to meet you, Mr. President, no matter the circumstances. I trust your first day in office has been a thrilling one. Peppers filled you in on my plan?

[[Your plan?]]


:: "Tug" the pull cord {"position":"1600,1700","size":"100,100"}
First use of dice roll mechanic. Must roll 3< to open up White House maintenance menu. If you roll 4>, just roll again and again until you get it.

White House maintenance menu opens up. Mechanics for this menu include:
-A clock ticking down for the maintenance of the generators (starts as a 2-clock)
-Temperature of the White House; currently 40 degrees; contingent on both power supply and fortification of the building against the elements (maybe the weather changes every day and has an effect on these systems)
-Power supply to WH; areas in the WH begin to shut down if the power fails
-Fortifications + insulation
-"Skill tree" for development of better energy systems, fortifications, insulation, etc; better systems make the 2-clock larger; better systems change the consequences of low dice rolls
-Starting dice roll for generators:
	-5 & 6 = fill up clock
    -3 & 4 = fill up half
    -1 & 2 = don't fill up and temperature falls 5 degrees
    
[[Thanks for showing me this. Any idea where my Surgeon is?]]


